All .md files should use GitHub Flavored Markdown (GFM).

All text in .md files is meant for ukrainian school students and should use ukrainian language.

All text meassages that are printed in code examples should use ukrainian language.

All .md files are written as short articles, explaining some aspect of Python programming language.

Top level headings of every .md file should match it's filename.

When describing new concept, give short and concise reason why and how this concept can be used.

When appropriate, code examples should be followed by execution results.

Code examples should use english names for variables and functions.

Style and terminology should be consistent across all .md files.

Refer to "outputting" as "друкування" in ukrainian.

`Залежності.md` Contains mermaid chart that visualizes dependencies between articles. Arrows point from dependent article toward article it depends on. The more independent article is - the higher it is placed on the chart. The more dependencies article has - the lower it is on the chart. All articles are mentioned in `README.md`. Every article lists all articles it depends on at the the top of the article.

Blocks of code that contain python code should specify language for syntax highlighting.

Code examples should be simple yet meaningful (ideally, related to real life situations).

Refer to flow diagram as "блок-схема".

Generate flow diagrams only when explicitly asked.

In flow diagrams use oval nodes for "start" and "end".

In flow diagrams combine `input()` and relevant `print()` command (with prompt) into one parallelogram node.

`exercises` folder contains coding exercises.

Every line of coding exercise code should be 40 characters or less.

Every coding exercise should end with 3 empty lines.

Refer to argument of a function or mentod as "аргумент" instead of "параметр".
